The Emory Digital Humanities Symposium is supported by [Emory Libraries](http://www.emory.edu/home/academics/libraries/index.html) and the [Emory Center for Digital Scholarship](http://digitalscholarship.emory.edu/) and is generously funded by the Emory University Libraries Innovation Grant; [Emory Conference Center Subvention Fund](http://cfde.emory.edu/); [Emory Laney Graduate School New Thinkers/New Leaders Fund](http://www.gs.emory.edu/about/special/new-thinkers.html); [Institute for Quantitative Theory and Methods](http://quantitative.emory.edu/); [Fox Center for Humanistic Inquiry](http://fchi.emory.edu/home/); Emory Center for Digital Scholarship; and [Middle Eastern and South Asian Studies](http://mesas.emory.edu/home/), [Religion](http://religion.emory.edu/home/index.html), and [Sociology](http://sociology.emory.edu/home/index.html) departments.
